The Internet Movie Database (IMDb) is a website that provides information on over 3.5 million movies, television shows, and video game titles. Users can rate each title on a scale from 1-10.

Create an IMDB clone using the full stack (AngularJS + Express + MongoDB).  Here are the requirements:

You should be able to enter a movie Title, Director, and Picture (link to an online picture).
You should support full CRUD for movies (Create, Read, Update, Delete).
The homepage should display a list of the top 5 movies listed in order of rating.
Users should be able to rate a movie with  a value between 1-10.
Extra Credit:

Add a list of actors for each movie (a one-to-many relationship).
Use FileStack.com to enable file uploads for the movie Picture.
Create a user registration/login system.
Require a user to login before rating a movie.
Use claims to prevent anyone except an Administrator from adding, updating, or deleting movies.
